<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
This is the most blatant example of the fundamental problem with allowing a class (any class) to have control over mobs of higher level.  I sincerely hope that the developers re-analyze the decision to allow this.  The only thing that allowed me to even hesitantly swallow it in the first place was their insistance that there was severe risk involved in charming something of greater level than you.  Unbroken control for 45 minutes does not constitute serious risk in my opinion.<P>This needs to be re-evaluated...<P>--------------------<P>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<BR>Dyzmond the Avalonian Sorcerer<BR>Member of the Furious Pantaloons<BR>Galahad Server<BR>Member of the Sorcerer Testing Team in Beta<BR>~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<P>"Who could ever calculate the path of a molecule?<BR>How do we know that the creations of worlds are not determined by falling grains of sand?"<BR>  --Victor Hugo, Les Miserables
